## What was requested

Add a diff/audit layer to gbatch_tools.py so every file write/delete by an
agent is saved as a reversible artifact before the action happens.

## What was actually built (commit f053eb6)

### Files modified
- bin/gemini-batch/gbatch_tools.py — core audit layer
- bin/claude-batch/cbatch_executor.py — sets _current_wo_id, calls mark_wo_done
- bin/claude-batch/cbatch_parallel.py — sets _current_wo_id, calls mark_wo_done

### Audit directory
logs/agent-diffs/ (auto-created on first use)

### File naming
{unixtime_ms}_{wo_id_slug}_{path_slug}.{ext}
  .patch    — unified diff for edits to existing files (revert with: patch -R < file.patch)
  .new      — full content of newly created files
  .deleted  — full content of files before deletion
  .DONE/.FAIL — zero-byte WO completion markers

### New public functions in gbatch_tools.py
- _current_wo_id: str — module-level var, set by executors before tool execution
- set_wo_context(wo_id) / clear_wo_context() — thread-safe alternative (threading.local)
- _slugify_wo_id(wo_id) — slug for filenames
- _path_to_slug(resolved_path) — relative path → filename slug
- _ensure_audit_dir() — creates logs/agent-diffs/
- _save_diff(old, new, path) — core audit writer, never raises
- mark_wo_done(wo_id, status) — writes DONE/FAIL marker file

### write_file changes
Before writing: reads old content if exists → calls _save_diff(old, new, path)
If new file: calls _save_diff(None, new, path)
Audit failure never blocks the actual write.

### delete_file changes
Before deleting: reads content → calls _save_diff(old, None, path)
Audit failure never blocks the actual delete.

